Customs officers of the Intellectual Property Investigation Bureau (IPIB) in Hong Kong, have busted up several illegal operations involving the shipment and illeagal distribution of optical dics.  Under the law such crimes are punishable by up to $50,000 in fines and up to four years' imprisonment.

Many busts resulted in some arrests.  Customs agents recovered thousands if not millions of dollars in equipment from each bust.

Things seized by IPIB Customs agents include, CDs, DVDs, VCDs and some equipment.

In one year alone, Customs officers seized 4.4 million pirated opitcal discs worth $140 million and arrested more than 1500 people.

